<DOC><DOCNO> AP900914-0085 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NY-09-14-90 0743EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Gulf-Iraq-Rationing     09-14 0205</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Gulf-Iraq-Rationing,0226</SECOND><HEAD>Iraq Orders Bread Rationing</HEAD><HEAD>With PM-Gulf Rdp, Bjt</HEAD><DATELINE>BAGHDAD, Iraq (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Iraq will begin rationing bread beginningSaturday, the ruling party's newspaper reported today, adding to alist of other basic food items being limited since a U.N. embargobegan.   The Ministry of Trade ordered all bakeries and bread shops onSaturday to observe the rationing announced earlier this month,which limits bread to three pieces per person per day, the BaathParty newspaper Al-Tharawa reported.   Iraqis must present bread coupons to designated bread shops toreceive their allocations, Al-Tharwa said.   According to the rationing system, each Iraqi will have accessto 13.2 pounds of wheat flour each month, in the form of flour orbread.   Large lines have formed at bread shops since the U.N.-imposedeconomic embargo against Iraq and Kuwait in reaction to the Iraqiinvasion of Kuwait on Aug. 2.   Iraq also has imposed a rationing system for other basic fooditems such as rice, sugar and cooking oil, as well as soap anddetergent.   President Saddam Hussein also has asked Iraqis to cut back ontheir consumption of meat and to prepare for belt-tightening tocope with the U.N.-imposed trade embargo.   The embargo prevents the import of goods as well as the exportof oil, Iraq's chief source of revenue.</TEXT></DOC>